(P= 0.000). CONCLUSIONS In summary, our results demonstrate a high frequency of CFTR mutations in CBAVD patients, and these exhibit evident ethnic differences. In addition, 5T allele and 5T/(TG)12{\_}13 may contribute to the increased risk for CBAVD, with the 5T penetrance probably being modulated by adjacent (TG)12{\_}13.},
author = {Yu, J. and Chen, Z. and Ni, Y. and Li, Z.},
doi = {10.1093/humrep/der377},
issn = {0268-1161},
journal = {Human Reproduction},
month = {jan},
number = {1},
pages = {25--35},
